This work is a combination of code under two GPL variants, so the terms below
govern the whole. Both license texts ship with this source:

    COPYING.GPL2   GNU General Public License, version 2
    COPYING.GPL3   GNU General Public License, version 3

THE COMBINED WORK (this core, and the FPGA bitstream built from it) IS
CONVEYED UNDER THE **GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE, VERSION 3 OR (AT YOUR
OPTION) ANY LATER VERSION.**

Why v3 and not v2
-----------------
Individual source files carry their own license notices, and they are not all
the same:

  * Most of the core — including the PSX_MiSTer base (Robert Peip) that this
    project derives from, and this project's own System 11 hardware
    implementations — is "GPL version 2 **or (at your option) any later
    version**".

  * Several files inherited from the MiSTer framework and the PSX_MiSTer base
    are "GPL version 3 **or any later version**":

        rtl/hps_ext.v      rtl/ddram.sv      rtl/sdram.sv
        sys/hps_io.sv      sys/scandoubler.v sys/ddr_svc.sv   sys/sd_card.sv

Because the "or any later version" clause lets GPLv2+ code be used under v3,
but GPLv3+ code cannot be conveyed under v2, the only license under which the
*combination* can lawfully be distributed is GPLv3 (or later). Each file
individually remains available to you under the terms in its own header.

Other components
----------------
  * sys/ascal.vhd — Avalon Scaler, TEMLIB (2018-2020). Distributed by its
    author under permissive terms ("This code can be freely distributed and
    used for any purpose"); GPL-compatible.

  * sys/pll_hdmi.v, sys/pll_cfg/pll_cfg.v and other PLL wrappers — generated
    by Intel/Altera Quartus and carrying Intel's copyright notice. They are
    the standard megafunction output required to target the Cyclone V device
    and are redistributed as generated, on the same terms as every other
    MiSTer core.

No warranty
